-- Blockbuster sells Game Station for $150 mln
-- 
-- Wed May 2, 2007 2:43am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/02/us-blockbuster-gamegroup-idUSWEN747120070502

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Blockbuster Inc. BBI.N said on Wednesday it had sold Game Station Ltd. to British-based Game Group Plc GMG.L for about $150 million in cash, subject to certain adjustments. 

 Blockbuster said it intends to use most of the money from the sale of Game Station, its 217-store speciality games retailer in the UK, to pay down debt.